    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-17T05:43:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-17T05:43:00-05:00" n="672"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d672">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4719</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJL1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-17T10:00:00-00:43">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1917, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received, 2.15 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Bacchante</hi> returned 15th to await instructions. Last night
                    large meeting of citizens from various sections of the Republic enthusiastically
                    endorsed action of Government concerning Germany without a dissenting vote.
                    Approval of citizens down coast also made known, including the Chief Justice.
                    The dominant note sounded was that no guaranty from the Government of the United
                    States was necessary because the attitude of the Government of the United States
                    towards Liberia in the past is a sufficient guaranty as to the future.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
